<subSubSection id="11D265234548B64AB595FACCFCD01B7B" pageId="11" pageNumber="470" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="597736A84548B64AB595FACCFA2C18A7" blockId="11.[151,1437,1333,1540]" pageId="11" pageNumber="470">
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA4548B64AB595FACCFE80180B" bold="true" box="[199,317,1369,1395]" pageId="11" pageNumber="470">Remarks:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="3D594B594548B64AB411FACFFDB2180C" author="Martynova, O. M." box="[323,527,1369,1396]" pageId="11" pageNumber="470" pagination="721 - 747" refId="ref15684" refString="Martynova, O. M. (1957) Skopionnitsy (Mecoptera) fauny SSSR. II Semeistvo Panorpidae. [Scorpion-flies (Mecoptera) of USSR fauna. II The family Panorpidae]. Entomologicheskoe obozrenie, 36 (3), 721 - 747. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1957">Martynova (1957)</bibRefCitation>
reported the presence of 
<specimenCount id="4FCEFD214548B64AB677FACFFC77180B" box="[805,970,1369,1396]" pageId="11" pageNumber="470" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName id="9EC84D2B4548B64AB6BFFACFFBD8180B" authorityName="MacLachlan" authorityYear="1869" box="[1005,1125,1370,1395]" class="Insecta" family="Panorpidae" genus="Panorpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="470" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="connexa">
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA4548B64AB6BFFACFFBD8180B" box="[1005,1125,1370,1395]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="470">P. connexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
housed in collection of ZIN RAS, labelled as “ЕлиЗаветград [ныне Кировоград], Херс. г. 20 v 91, Яцентковский” [
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA4548B64AB1DCFAE8FC6E18C3" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="470">
Elisavethrad town [now Kirovograd], Khersonska huberniya, 
<date id="2D7610684548B64AB713FA34FD7F18C3" box="[577,706,1441,1467]" pageId="11" pageNumber="470" value="1891-05-20">20.05.1891</date>
, leg. A.V. Yatsentkovskii
</emphasis>
] and concluded that the label is correct. 
<bibRefCitation id="3D594B594548B64AB5C5FA50FEED1898" author="Willmann, R." box="[151,336,1477,1504]" pageId="11" pageNumber="470" pagination="543 - 564" refId="ref17121" refString="Willmann, R. (1975) Die Gattung Panorpa in der Turkei. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, 79, 543 - 564." type="journal article" year="1975">Willmann (1975</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="3D594B594548B64AB40EFA50FE1E18A7" author="Willmann, R." box="[348,419,1477,1503]" pageId="11" pageNumber="470" pagination="517 - 523" refId="ref17148" refString="Willmann, R. (1978 a) Bemerkungen zu anatolischen Mecopteren. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, 81, 517 - 523." type="journal article" year="1978">1978a</bibRefCitation>
) reported 
<taxonomicName id="9EC84D2B4548B64AB747FA53FD3318A7" authorityName="MacLachlan" authorityYear="1869" box="[533,654,1478,1503]" class="Insecta" family="Panorpidae" genus="Panorpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="470" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="connexa">
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA4548B64AB747FA53FD3318A7" box="[533,654,1478,1503]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="470">P. connexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only from the Caucasus and northern 
<collectingCountry id="21DF76384548B64AB168FA50FB3718A7" box="[1082,1162,1477,1503]" name="Turkey" pageId="11" pageNumber="470">Turkey</collectingCountry>
along the Caspian Sea.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="597736A84548B64AB595FA7CFCD01B7B" blockId="11.[151,1437,1333,1540]" box="[199,877,1513,1540]" pageId="11" pageNumber="470">
The presence of 
<taxonomicName id="9EC84D2B4548B64AB4D3FA7FFE441B7B" authorityName="MacLachlan" authorityYear="1869" box="[385,505,1514,1539]" class="Insecta" family="Panorpidae" genus="Panorpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="470" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="connexa">
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA4548B64AB4D3FA7FFE441B7B" box="[385,505,1514,1539]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="470">P. connexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="21DF76384548B64AB74CFA7CFDC51B7B" box="[542,632,1513,1539]" name="Ukraine" pageId="11" pageNumber="470">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
should be confirmed.
</paragraph>
